<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY OVER BILINGUAL EDUCATION IN L.A. SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If bilingual teaching has proven to make a positive difference then our schools 
should have it. But why pay up to $5,000 a year more to just these teachers? 
Instead, let's raise the salaries of all L.A. teachers to the point where Los 
Angeles attracts the best and keeps the best! 
</P>
<P>
SUE MATUS 
</P>
<P>
Westchester 
</P>
