<P>
DEVELOPER FINED FOR BUILDING VIOLATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Developer Abby Sher has pleaded no contest to one count of violating Santa 
Monica building codes and paid a $562 fine. Another 14 counts against her were 
dismissed. 
</P>
<P>
Sher's legal troubles stemmed from her controversial Edgemar complex on Santa 
Monica's Main Street, built to house shops, a restaurant and the private Santa 
Monica Museum of Art. City prosecutors accused Sher of allowing the complex to 
be used for art shows and other events before obtaining proper permits. 
</P>
<P>
In her plea, filed this week in Municipal Court, Sher did not contest one count 
that she improperly allowed a UCLA program to use the building last June. Sher 
also agreed to provide all lessees in the complex with written copies of the 
city's noise ordinance. 
