<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST : LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
PUBLIC MEETINGS SET ON METRO RAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rapid Transit District has scheduled two public meetings to discuss benefit 
assessment districts for the second phase of the Metro Rail project. The route 
of Phase 2 goes as far west as Wilshire Boulevard and Western Avenue in the 
Mid-Wilshire district, and as far north as North Hollywood. Input from the 
meetings will be given to a task force that will advise policy makers on 
benefit assessment districts for Phase 2. Assessments from the private sector 
are expected to generate about $75 million, or 5% of the total funds, toward 
the cost of building Phase 2. 
</P>
<P>
The first meeting is scheduled for 7:30 p.m. March 16 in the main meeting room 
at the Hollywood Senior Multipurpose Center, 6501 Fountain Ave. The second is 
at 1 p.m. March 21 at the Los Angeles City College Student Center, 855 N. 
Vermont Ave. 
</P>
</TEXT>
