<P>
9 PRIESTS, 4 NUNS MAKE IT TO THE FINISH IN MARATHON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nine Catholic priests and four nuns were among 19 Catholics to finish the Los 
Angeles Marathon Sunday, but another 20 or so in the "vocations-promoting" 
contingent from the archdiocese wilted in the heat over the grueling 26.2-mile 
course. 
</P>
<P>
Father George Aguilera of Hacienda Heights led the males with a time of 3 hours 
and 17 minutes, and Dominican Sister Mary Sean ran in 4:50.0. Seminarian Felipe 
Regaldo was timed at 3:21.17. Bishop Carl Fisher ran 8 miles before leaving to 
catch a plane. 
</P>
