<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOW, IT'S 'GET ON YOUR MARK, GET SET, LIE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With regard to Charlie Francis' March 1 mention of former and present abusers 
of steroids, I am absolutely certain that neither Evelyn Ashford nor her former 
coach, three-time Olympian Pat Connolly would ever use any 
performance-enhancing drug of any kind. 
</P>
<P>
I have known Evelyn since her last year in high school (1975) as a competitor, 
teammate and friend. I've traveled and trained with her and know her personal 
convictions on the use of such drugs, and she is vehemently against it. 
</P>
<P>
Her talent has never required artificial stimulation. She got her records the 
old-fashioned way. She earned them. 
</P>
<P>
As for Pat Connolly, my association with her began in '75 when she re-entered 
the women's track and field program she herself initiated in '73 at UCLA. She 
has been my mentor and friend ever since. She is a longtime opponent of drug 
use, and I and many other honest people are stunned and outraged by Francis' 
attempt to implicate Pat and Evelyn in his illegal and reprehensible coaching 
practices. 
</P>
<P>
KARIN SMITH 
</P>
<P>
Four-time Olympian (javelin) 
</P>
<P>
Salem, Ore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
