<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
KENNEDY OUTRUNS TAFT BY WINNING 11 EVENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although the Kennedy High boys' track team was devastated by 25 academic 
ineligibilities several weeks ago, the Golden Cougars still have a talented -- 
albeit small -- squad. They lack quantity, but not quality. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy demonstrated quality in a 73-54 victory over visiting Taft on Friday in 
a Northwest Valley Conference meet. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy's victory overshadowed a brilliant performance by Taft's Greg Sheets, 
who won the pole vault with a personal best of 15 feet, 1 inch. Sheets, the 
runner-up to Jay Bettinger of Chatsworth in last year's City Section 
championships, had a previous best of 15-0. 
</P>
<P>
Antiwaun Carter, Jorge Duran, Patrick Blake and Cord Bailey were all 
instrumental in Kennedy's win as the Golden Cougars (2-0) won 11 of 15 events 
and nine of 10 track events. 
</P>
<P>
Carter won the 100 meters in 11.4 and the 220 yards in 23.5, and anchored the 
victorious 440 relay (46.3). Duran won the mile (4:39.8) and two mile 
(10:14.7); Blake won the 120-yard high hurdles in 16.9 and the 330 intermediate 
hurdles in 44.6. Bailey won the triple jump at 40-6 and placed second in the 
high jump (5-10) and second in the long jump (20-0). 
</P>
<P>
In other boys' meets: 
</P>
<P>
Reseda 70, North Hollywood 53 -- Aaron Brumfield won the triple jump and high 
jump for Reseda (4-0, 2-0) in the Valley Pac-8 Conference meet at North 
Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando 74, Canoga Park 43 -- The host Tigers were led in the Northwest 
Valley Conference meet by Ibed Aguirre, who won the mile (4:51.9) and two mile 
(10:22.8), and Howard McCrary, who won the 120-yard high hurdles (15.7) and 
triple jump (42-3 1/2). 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham 113, Sylmar 10 -- Brian Gastelum won three events for host 
Birmingham (2-0) in the Valley Pac-8 Conference meet. Gastelum, a junior, won 
the 800 in a personal best of 2:00.6, the 1,600 in 4:50.0 and the 3,200 in 
10:29.3. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' TRACK 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 61, Taft 48 -- Taft won seven of 13 events, but the Golden Cougars' 
superior depth prevailed in the Northwest Valley Conference meet at Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
Natasha Como and Lela Lemell helped Kennedy dominate the sprints. 
</P>
<P>
Como won the 100 meters in 13.0, the 220 yards in 27.9 and anchored the 
victorious 440 relay (53.0). Lemell, a sophomore, won the 440 in 1:04.3. 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills 63, El Camino Real 45 -- Shaunte Parker won two individual events 
and anchored two victorious relays for host Granada Hills in the Northwest 
Valley Conference meet. 
</P>
<P>
Poly 66, Van Nuys 38 -- Tina Means led Van Nuys (2-0) in the Valley Pac-8 
Conference meet at Poly by winning the 110-meter low hurdles, the 330-yard lows 
and the high jump. 
</P>
